\title{Hub Trees}
\taxon{section}
\date{2026-04-04}
\tag{transclusion}
\meta{description}{The 5 skills with highest transclusion in-degree}

\import{macros}

\p{Five trees absorb most inbound references. Every random walk through the connected component passes through at least one.}

\table{
\tr{\th{Hub}\th{In-degree}\th{Role}}
\tr{\td{[[gay-mcp]]}\td{68}\td{Universal seed — deterministic color for every skill}}
\tr{\td{[[bisimulation-game]]}\td{34}\td{Behavioral equivalence checker}}
\tr{\td{[[acsets]]}\td{24}\td{Attributed C-Set data model}}
\tr{\td{[[triad-interleave]]}\td{21}\td{GF(3) composition operator}}
\tr{\td{[[spi-parallel-verify]]}\td{15}\td{Strong Parallelism Invariant checker}}
}

\subtree{
\title{gay-mcp (68 references)}
\p{Every skill that generates deterministic output references \code{\startverb gay-mcp\stopverb}. It is the seed from which colors, trits, fingerprints, and SPI traces grow. Removing it disconnects 68 skills.}
\p{Transclusion target: SplitMix64 algorithm, GF(3) trit derivation from hue, color chain generation.}
}

\subtree{
\title{bisimulation-game (34 references)}
\p{The attacker-defender game for proving two systems behave identically. Referenced whenever a skill claims behavioral equivalence — version migrations, skill updates, protocol changes.}
\p{Transclusion target: game rules, partition refinement, distinguishing trace extraction.}
}

\subtree{
\title{acsets (24 references)}
\p{Attributed C-Sets from AlgebraicJulia. The categorical database model underlying messaging-world, browser-history, DuckDB schemas, and all relational skill data.}
\p{Transclusion target: schema definition via \code{\startverb @present\stopverb}, morphism types, attribute declaration.}
}

\subtree{
\title{triad-interleave (21 references)}
\p{The composition operator. Takes three streams (MINUS, ERGODIC, PLUS) and interleaves them into a balanced schedule. Every GF(3)-conserved workflow routes through this.}
}

\subtree{
\title{spi-parallel-verify (15 references)}
\p{Verifies Strong Parallelism Invariance: three parallel color streams produce identical results regardless of interleaving order. The soundness check.}
}
